==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Molehill
<hw>Mole"hill`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A little hillock of
earth thrown up by moles working under ground; hence, a very small hill,
or an insignificant obstacle or difficulty; <as>as, to make a mountain
out of a <ex>molehill</ex></as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Having leapt over such mountains, lie down before a
<qex>molehill</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>South.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><-- p. 937 --></p>

<p><ent>molendinarious</ent>⟦br⟧
